SUMMARY:What's Stored in the Body? A Breathwork Mini-Journey
DESCRIPTION:This workshop is a relaxed\, supportive space for folks to dip 
 their toes into the wild world of integrative breathwork. What is Breathwo
 rk?Breathwork is blowing up as a buzzword these days. It’s a broad term 
 that covers different breathing techniques and methodologies for having po
 werful and healing experiences by modifying the way we breathe. Integrativ
 e breathwork in particular is a type of breathwork that uses relaxation an
 d paying attention to our breathing to surface and work through unconsciou
 s content that we haven’t fully processed yet.&nbsp\;Why it matters?Brea
 thing underpins our mental\, emotional\, social\, and physical lives\, and
  yet so few of us have a relationship to our own breathing or have taken t
 he time to unpack our breathing patterns. We didn’t grow up knowing how 
 to breathe optimally\, and we didn’t learn about the ways our experience
 s taught our bodies how to breathe (or as is often the case\, how not to b
 reathe). So we miss out on the information that comes to us along every in
 hale and exhale\, and the chance to shift our internal experience using ju
 st our breath.&nbsp\;About the WorkshopThis workshop is for folks who are 
 curious about breathwork and learning more about what is possible by payin
 g better attention to their breathing. It is not a full breathwork journey
  - it includes three rounds of guided breathing experiential exercises (mi
 ni-journeys) with time to talk about your experiences in between each roun
 d. We’ll cover breathing observation methods\, how to respond to your br
 eathing patterns\, and experience some of the pathways of connection that 
 breathing opens up.&nbsp\;All are welcome\, even those who have never thou
 ght once about their own breathing! Come wearing comfy clothes and bring a
  water bottle and your own yoga mat or blanket if you have one. Note packe
 ts will be provided.&nbsp\;About the facilitatorEm Chiappinelli (she/they)
  is a breathwork facilitator and event organizer who lives in a rural farm
 ing community in northern Virginia. She has been in long-term training (1\
 ,000+ hrs) for integrative breathwork across multiple training schools and
  programs\, and believes that breathing needs to be the first go-to tool i
 n anyone’s inner work\, interpersonal\, or survival strategies (includin
 g her own!). Em facilitates breathwork sessions for individuals virtually 
 and in-person\, and you can read more about the sessions here or reach out
  directly at hello@everydayalive.com.What Is an Olio?Think Olio is an ongo
 ing experiment in lifelong learning.We are a community of open-minded peop
 le who gather to exchange ideas with new friends and connect over art\, li
 terature\, and philosophy.An Olio is what we call the social learning even
 ts we’ve been organizing since 2015. Olios are led by a teacher who love
 s sharing their passions and the room is filled with curious\, open-minded
  New Yorkers.&nbsp\;Our goal is to spark new perspectives\, ignite curiosi
 ty\, and enjoy ourselves socially—an alternative to typical nightlife op
 tions.Disclaimer: By purchasing a ticket\, you agree to have your photo/vi
 deo used for social media/marketing materials. If you prefer to not have y
 our photo taken\, feel free to send us a note. Photo by the unparalleled E
 rin Pearlman.\n\nTickets & info: https://www.viewcy.com/event/whats_stored
 _in_the
URL:https://www.viewcy.com/event/whats_stored_in_the
END:VEVENT
